    <title>The pop factory</title>
    <link>https://shafrasier.com/map/MUSIC/IDEAS/The-pop-factory</link>
    <guid>https://shafrasier.com/map/MUSIC/IDEAS/The-pop-factory</guid>
    <description><![CDATA[ Theodor Adorno argued in On Popular Music that the culture industry standardizes its products: every hit follows a pre-given pattern, and the variations between individual songs are surface differences designed to mask that uniformity. ]]></description>
